******
[1] Denmark: 3rd mink farm infected by COVID-19
Date: Wed 1 Jul 2020
Source: Danish Ministry of the Environment and Food, press release [in Danish, machine trans., edited]
https://www.foedevarestyrelsen.dk/Nyheder/Aktuelt/Sider/Nyheder%202020/Fødevarestyrelsen-finder-COVID-19-i-en-3--nordjysk-mink-besætning.aspx


The Danish Veterinary and Food Administration finds COVID-19 in a 3rd North Jutland mink herd

A mink herd in Hjorring municipality [North Jutland; map at https://tinyurl.com/y8mw7h82] with approx. 5000 mink is infected with COVID-19. The government has decided that the herd should be killed for reasons of precaution. The Food Board on Monday [29 Jun 2020] sampled the herd. This was because people related to the mink farm told the Food Authority that they were found infected with COVID-19. The test results show that more than 50% of the herd is infected with COVID-19.

The mink farm is located in an area where the local population has been affected by a virus strain that has led to the killing of 2 mink herds. It is not yet clear whether the 3rd infected farm is infected with the same virus strain.

It is against this background that the government has decided that this 3rd infected herd must also be killed on the basis of a precautionary principle. The National Board of Food expects the herd to be killed on Friday [3 Jul 2020].

None of the 3 infected herds are among the approx. 120 mink farms included in a national screening for COVID-19.

--
Communicated by:
