[Since 17 Jun 2020, the Danish competent authority in animal health reported the infection of 2 other mink farms in the same area. Also, in the 1st infected farm, a family dog was tested positive for SARS-CoV-2. It is the 1st finding in pets in Denmark. More information about this event can be found in ProMED post archive no. 20200624.7506728.

Denmark is the 2nd country, after the Netherlands, to report infection with SARS-CoV-2 in farmed mink. - Mod.SF

HealthMap/ProMED map of Denmark: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7536980,66913]

******
[2] Netherlands: 18th mink farm infected by COVID-19
Date: Fri 3 Jul 2020
Source: Al Arabiya, Agence France-Presse (AFP) report [edited]
https://english.alarabiya.net/en/coronavirus/2020/07/03/Coronavirus-New-COVID-19-infection-found-on-mink-farm-in-Netherlands


Dutch authorities announced Friday [3 Jul 2020] that yet another mink farm has been infected with the novel coronavirus, making 18 in total, with thousands of animals to be culled.

The outbreak was reported on a farm at Landhorst [North Brabant] in the southeast, the Health Ministry said in a statement, in the same region where 17 other farms were also infected.

"The infection was discovered because the mink showed symptoms of the disease, and farmers are obliged to report it," the ministry said.

The farm, which has more than 4300 animals "will be cleared as soon as possible," it added.

The Netherlands first reported in April [2020] that 2 mink farms had been infected with the COVID-19 disease.

At least 2 workers were also infected in what the World Health Organization said could be the 1st known animal-to-human transmissions.

Last month [June 2020] authorities culled thousands of mink on farms infected by the coronavirus.

The farming of mink for fur is a controversial subject in the Netherlands, where all mink farms will have to be phased out by 2024.

Last week [week of 22 Jun 2020] Dutch MPs voted overwhelmingly in favor of shutting mink farms by the end of the year [2020], with the government saying it was working on plans to help farmers close down the farms.

The Netherlands has reported more than 50 000 coronavirus infections [in humans], with more than 6100 deaths, according to official figures.

